5|$|Igbo Landing (alternatively {{written as}} Ibo Landing, Ebo Landing, or Ebos Landing) is a {{historic}} site at Dunbar Creek on St. Simons Island, Glynn County, Georgia. It was the setting of a mass suicide in 1803 by captive Igbo people who had taken control of their slave ship and refused to submit <b>to</b> <b>slavery</b> in the United States. The event's moral value as a story of resistance towards slavery has symbolic importance in African American folklore and literary history.|$|E
