5|$|King {{stated that}} black Americans, {{as well as}} other {{disadvantaged}} Americans, should be compensated for historical wrongs. In an interview conducted for Playboy in 1965, he said that granting black Americans only equality could not realistically close the economic gap between them and whites. King said that he did not seek a full restitution of wages lost <b>to</b> <b>slavery,</b> which he believed impossible, but proposed a government compensatory program of $50billion over ten years to all disadvantaged groups.|$|E
